<TITLE> Govt panel on BDR mutiny finalises findings </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka , May 12 (bdnews24.com) The probe committee formed by the government on BDR mutiny has prepared a report, committee chief Anisuzzaman says. "We are ready to file it whenever the government asks," he told bdnews24.com on Tuesday afternoon. Asked if there is any possibility of further extension of the deadline, he said, "We have not asked for any time extension." The latest deadline for submission of report expires on Tuesday. The government extended deadline until Mar 30. Earlier in the day, additional home secretary Golam Hossain, also the committee member-secretary, told bdnews24.com that they had prepared the report. On Feb 26, the national committee was formed with home minister at the helm to probe the bloody Feb 25-26 mutiny by the border guards at their Peelkhana headquarters. On Mar 2, the committee was reconstituted with former bureaucrat Anisuzzaman as the chief. The deadline for submission of the government probe committee report was Mar 9 but the time was extended by seven more working days. On the final date of report submission on Mar 23, the last date was stretched by more four working days. The government then extended deadline on Mar 30 for another 30 working days at the request of the committee in the interest of fair investigation. The chief coordinator of probe committees, commerce minister Faruq Khan, said the government will go public with the findings of the panel at a proper time. bd
